In a large skillet over medium heat, warm oil and cook chicken for 5 to 10 minutes or until no longer pink. Turn heat to low. Add sour cream, half and half, cumin, nutmeg, allspice, and ground white pepper to skillet; simmer for about 5 minutes or until sauce is smooth. Do not allow mixture to boil. Stir stewed tomatoes into the mixture and simmer over low heat for 10 minutes; serve.